definitions.definition: The organic compound acetylene . The simplest alkyne , a colorless gaseous (at room temperature and pressure ) hydrocarbon with the chemical formula HC≡CH or C 2 H 2 .

main_definition: ( organic chemistry , official IUPAC name ) The organic compound acetylene . The simplest alkyne , a colorless gaseous (at room temperature and pressure ) hydrocarbon with the chemical formula HC≡CH or C 2 H 2 .
